Date: Wed, 19 Mar 2008 18:09:20 -0700
From: 	akepner@sgi ...
Subject: [PATCH 2/3 v5] dma/ia64: update ia64 machvecs, swiotlb.c
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2008/3/19/596

Change all ia64 machvecs to use the new dma_*map*_attrs()
interfaces. Implement the old dma_*map_*() interfaces in
terms of the corresponding new interfaces. For ia64/sn, make
use of one dma attribute, DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER. Introduce 
swiotlb_*map*_attrs() functions.
Signed-off-by: Arthur Kepner <akepner@sgi.com>
---
